discrepancies.pdf_value: This message provides a log of past signal security related events, that is, events related to jamming and spoofing. Each event is a combination of a detection type and a event type, where the event type 'indication started' and 'indication stopped' and also the event type 'indication triggered' and 'indication timed-out' form a pair. A maximum of 16 events are logged; after the log is filled, recent events take precedence over past events in the log. Power cycles and restarts of the receiver reset the log, deleting its content. Note: It is advised not to restart the receiver while it's indicating spoofing.
